WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.045 --> 00:00:05.980
The last semester in high school...

2
00:00:06.915 --> 00:00:08.644
...only comes around once.

3
00:00:14.122 --> 00:00:19.651
l haven't really been on too many dates
in the last 16 or 17 years.

4
00:00:20.596 --> 00:00:22.757
l hope l do okay.

5
00:00:25.734 --> 00:00:27.725
You'll do great.

6
00:00:31.473 --> 00:00:33.839
Slide over. You drive.

7
00:01:05.641 --> 00:01:08.667
Nice Expo. Problem is. it's a '98.

8
00:01:08.844 --> 00:01:11.677
What the hell do you know about cars?

9
00:01:17.653 --> 00:01:19.052
Well...

10
00:01:20.255 --> 00:01:23.691
...'98s. there's a little shortage
in the battery cable.

11
00:01:23.859 --> 00:01:27.124
lt's nothing a rubber insulation
can't fix. though.

12
00:01:27.996 --> 00:01:29.486
Pulling out a condom.

13
00:01:37.172 --> 00:01:39.606
Go ahead. check it out.
Give it a try.

14
00:01:39.808 --> 00:01:42.106
You're gonna fix my car with a rubber?

15
00:01:54.923 --> 00:01:56.288
Yeah.

16
00:02:12.207 --> 00:02:16.974
When you were doing your thizzle earlier.
you were off the hizzle.

17
00:02:17.179 --> 00:02:19.773
Yeah. What kind of car do you drizzle?

18
00:02:21.116 --> 00:02:23.676
-Drizzle--?
-He's designing and constructing one...

19
00:02:23.885 --> 00:02:25.182
...from the ground up...

20
00:02:25.587 --> 00:02:28.750
...which. as of yet. has no reference
in layman's terms.

21
00:02:28.824 --> 00:02:32.225
Yeah. so basically. you don't have a car.

22
00:02:33.295 --> 00:02:36.287
Well. l never had a rich pops
to buy me anything...

23
00:02:37.232 --> 00:02:40.167
...so l'm just a working man
trying to come up.

24
00:02:40.802 --> 00:02:43.168
Yeah. you cool. man.

25
00:02:44.606 --> 00:02:46.836
l'm not feeling this cat.

26
00:03:02.090 --> 00:03:05.719
So let me tell you about the time
when l was fixing this police car...

27
00:03:05.927 --> 00:03:09.795
...on the side of the highway.
She had that outfit on. the brown one--

28
00:03:10.932 --> 00:03:13.696
-Hey. baby.
-l need to talk to you.

29
00:03:13.869 --> 00:03:15.234
Now.

30
00:03:15.837 --> 00:03:17.702
Fellas. y'all have to excuse me.

31
00:03:19.641 --> 00:03:22.701
You are a genius! This is working great!
You're so brilliant.

32
00:03:25.414 --> 00:03:27.848
-You look upset.
-l am.

33
00:03:28.417 --> 00:03:30.942
-At what?
-While you were fronting...

34
00:03:31.119 --> 00:03:34.213
...like you're some player.
l was outside waiting for you.

35
00:03:34.389 --> 00:03:36.823
We have a deal.

36
00:03:36.892 --> 00:03:39.918
-We walk the hall together. remember?
-Sorry--

37
00:03:45.767 --> 00:03:50.227
Look. Alvin. l think you're starting
to feel yourself a little too much.

38
00:03:50.405 --> 00:03:52.737
l do not do that.
My mother said you'll go blind!

39
00:03:52.908 --> 00:03:54.273
Whatever.

40
00:03:55.977 --> 00:03:59.743
Look. just don't ever
keep me waiting again.

41
00:04:10.325 --> 00:04:12.850
-Hey. we'll catch up with y'all.
-All right. guys.

42
00:04:13.028 --> 00:04:15.087
l can't believe this. dude....

43
00:04:16.331 --> 00:04:17.958
What's the matter?
l mean. l said l was sorry.

44
00:04:18.166 --> 00:04:20.657
l got caught up.
l was hanging with my friends--

45
00:04:20.802 --> 00:04:23.100
The friends who gave you
a pepperoni facial?

46
00:04:23.271 --> 00:04:25.102
Look. we squashed all that.

47
00:04:25.273 --> 00:04:28.003
lt's a lot of work. Alvin.
The whole interior.

48
00:04:28.176 --> 00:04:30.007
We wanted you to be there.

49
00:04:30.178 --> 00:04:31.338
Okay. look.

50
00:04:31.713 --> 00:04:34.682
We'll get together this weekend.
we'll work on the car.

51
00:04:34.816 --> 00:04:37.842
lt'll be like old times.
We'll have a good time.

52
00:04:37.919 --> 00:04:42.151
Great. Friday night. We'll get to work on
reupholstering the inside of the seats--

53
00:04:42.357 --> 00:04:44.791
Friday. Friday....

54
00:04:44.960 --> 00:04:48.293
-l can't do it. l got plans.
-Well. Saturday. then.

55
00:04:48.997 --> 00:04:51.329
Saturday's not good for me either.

56
00:04:51.733 --> 00:04:53.826
You know what?
Sunday afternoon.

57
00:04:54.369 --> 00:04:56.030
Yeah. Great. Sunday.

58
00:04:59.307 --> 00:05:00.467
Yeah.

59
00:05:01.376 --> 00:05:03.867
-Gonna introduce me?
-You met them in fourth grade. remember?

60
00:05:03.945 --> 00:05:05.970
What's going on?

61
00:05:06.948 --> 00:05:08.939
What's the deal?

62
00:05:09.217 --> 00:05:11.481
Life is good. You all right?

63
00:05:42.317 --> 00:05:43.841
Hello?

64
00:05:45.220 --> 00:05:46.778
Paris?

65
00:05:47.789 --> 00:05:50.314
Yo. Paris!

66
00:06:06.174 --> 00:06:09.041
What are you doing
just walking in my house?

67
00:06:10.445 --> 00:06:13.881
The door was open. My bad.

68
00:06:14.049 --> 00:06:17.018
l heard you playing your guitar. though.
lt sound hot.

69
00:06:18.119 --> 00:06:20.178
What are you even doing here?

70
00:06:21.456 --> 00:06:25.449
lt's the last day in our two-week contract.
l thought we'd hang out.

71
00:06:27.329 --> 00:06:29.263
Let me hear you play.

72
00:06:32.467 --> 00:06:34.332
Come on.

73
00:06:36.605 --> 00:06:39.039
Look. l'm still learning...

74
00:06:39.207 --> 00:06:44.270
...and the lyrics l wrote
don't go with my melody yet.

75
00:06:49.184 --> 00:06:52.210
l'll read. You play.

76
00:06:55.991 --> 00:06:57.822
Come on.

77
00:07:19.381 --> 00:07:21.576
"And l rise.

78
00:07:22.584 --> 00:07:26.145
ln spite of my fear inside...

79
00:07:26.454 --> 00:07:29.355
...caused by those who have burned me
with their lies.

80
00:07:30.358 --> 00:07:32.383
And l rise.

81
00:07:48.543 --> 00:07:50.340
And l rise."

82
00:07:57.452 --> 00:07:59.147
Look....

83
00:08:02.223 --> 00:08:04.885
Go on. get dressed.

84
00:08:05.226 --> 00:08:06.625
Why?

85
00:08:07.395 --> 00:08:11.491
No more questions. Get dressed.

86
00:08:35.256 --> 00:08:37.247
To my relationships that didn't work

87
00:08:37.425 --> 00:08:40.121
Map of this human heart
Starts at the age of 15

88
00:08:40.195 --> 00:08:42.356
When I lost my virginity
To a lady. older

89
00:08:42.564 --> 00:08:45.158
Like most boys
It was based on the lies I told her

90
00:08:45.366 --> 00:08:48.699
I had so much to prove
Like I had more experience

91
00:08:49.604 --> 00:08:51.367
Than she thought I knew
And though it wasn't true

92
00:08:51.539 --> 00:08:52.699
It was amazing

93
00:08:53.608 --> 00:08:55.405
But it ended because I did
What most young boys do

94
00:08:55.610 --> 00:08:58.579
Listened to the lies of a fool
Which led to this girl

95
00:08:58.980 --> 00:09:01.107
Getting socked in the jaw
In the middle of school

96
00:09:01.282 --> 00:09:03.443
Even though I didn't do it
I felt to blame

97
00:09:03.618 --> 00:09:07.179
Because the girl who hit her was the cousin
Of my man who was salting my game

98
00:09:07.355 --> 00:09:09.323
Nowadays it just don't seem cool

99
00:09:09.491 --> 00:09:11.482
Tell me what the hell
Am I supposed to do?

100
00:09:11.659 --> 00:09:14.150
And then a wise man gave me a clue

101
00:09:14.229 --> 00:09:17.528
He said
"The only way out is the way through "

102
00:09:19.334 --> 00:09:21.564
You know. it's silly...

103
00:09:22.270 --> 00:09:24.500
...but instead of this whole...

104
00:09:25.373 --> 00:09:29.070
..."drill team/Dru Hilton's girl" thing...

105
00:09:29.677 --> 00:09:34.512
...what l really. really always dream about
is just going somewhere.

106
00:09:36.551 --> 00:09:38.746
Somewhere where nobody knows me.

107
00:09:39.120 --> 00:09:41.714
Just being this girl with. like.
crazy cool dreads...

108
00:09:42.357 --> 00:09:46.453
...and a guitar and--
Oh. never mind. it's really dumb.

109
00:09:50.398 --> 00:09:51.763
You know...

110
00:09:52.667 --> 00:09:54.328
...you could bring your guitar here.

111
00:09:56.571 --> 00:09:59.335
No. l can't.

112
00:10:01.543 --> 00:10:06.003
No. you mean you won't.

113
00:10:23.531 --> 00:10:25.795
This is beautiful.

114
00:10:30.605 --> 00:10:32.664
You know. Al...

115
00:10:33.374 --> 00:10:38.402
...there's something
that we've been avoiding all day.

116
00:10:38.580 --> 00:10:41.378
Something that maybe we ought to do.

117
00:10:42.550 --> 00:10:44.609
You know what. you're right.

118
00:10:44.819 --> 00:10:47.617
This might sound kind of silly...

119
00:10:49.791 --> 00:10:51.759
...but how do we do it?

120
00:10:52.760 --> 00:10:54.284
Well....

121
00:10:55.663 --> 00:10:59.326
Just go for it. you know?
Just do it.

122
00:11:01.803 --> 00:11:03.327
Okay.

123
00:11:10.111 --> 00:11:13.342
We'll break up first thing
tomorrow morning.

124
00:11:13.414 --> 00:11:18.351
ln the hallway. so everybody can see.
l mean. make a big scene.

125
00:11:18.553 --> 00:11:23.490
But a dignified scene because.
you know. we gotta protect our reps.

126
00:11:23.691 --> 00:11:27.422
Did you hear what l just said?
Our reps!

127
00:11:28.329 --> 00:11:31.787
Al Johnson has a rep to protect!

128
00:11:33.902 --> 00:11:35.802
Player. player.

129
00:11:37.138 --> 00:11:41.837
Come on. girl. put a pep in your step.
We got school in the morning!

130
00:12:22.350 --> 00:12:26.411
Now. those are the benefits of being raised
in a household with vinyl and 8-track.

131
00:12:26.621 --> 00:12:31.320
-You know. old school for real.
-Damn. man. you got all the 411.

132
00:12:31.392 --> 00:12:33.417
l'm talking Earth. Wind and Fire.

133
00:12:33.628 --> 00:12:36.461
-"Erf." E with a F at the end of it.
-Al?

134
00:12:36.664 --> 00:12:39.531
-Here comes your girl.
-Al. l need to talk to you.

135
00:12:39.701 --> 00:12:42.397
Don't you see grown men
are talking here?

136
00:12:43.938 --> 00:12:48.307
Anyway. you know. as l was saying.
you know. Ohio Players--

137
00:12:48.509 --> 00:12:50.500
Al. we need to talk.

138
00:12:50.678 --> 00:12:54.808
What's up with this "we. we" stuff?
This ain't French class. Ain't no "we."

139
00:12:55.350 --> 00:12:56.715
l'm a free agent now.

140
00:12:59.387 --> 00:13:03.483
-That was cruel.
-Sometimes you gotta be cruel to be kind.

141
00:13:03.925 --> 00:13:06.951
That's how you keep a lady in check.
you know what l'm saying?

142
00:13:09.964 --> 00:13:11.625
You still here?

143
00:13:11.833 --> 00:13:14.631
Bounce. Giddyup.

144
00:13:15.403 --> 00:13:17.428
Damn.

145
00:13:17.605 --> 00:13:20.438
Too many fish in the sea
for her to be hounding me.

146
00:13:20.608 --> 00:13:23.304
-l'm feeling this.
-l hear you. boy.

147
00:13:23.511 --> 00:13:25.342
She gonna be back too. Watch.

148
00:13:25.546 --> 00:13:28.811
Did you just see
how he just dogged Paris?

149
00:13:29.550 --> 00:13:33.384
-l want a strong brother like that.
-Yep.

150
00:13:33.454 --> 00:13:38.619
Look at him. standing there looking
better than a butter-leather Prada bag.

151
00:14:01.916 --> 00:14:05.249
You got a lot of nerve dissing me
the way you did.

152
00:14:06.888 --> 00:14:10.483
Yeah. l know. that's why
l came by. to apologize.

153
00:14:10.658 --> 00:14:12.751
But. yo. Oscar goes to you.

154
00:14:16.798 --> 00:14:20.666
Hey. l just really want to say thank you
for a great couple of weeks.

155
00:14:20.835 --> 00:14:23.429
Well. l was just doing
what l said l would do.

156
00:14:23.504 --> 00:14:24.835
And it worked.

157
00:14:25.006 --> 00:14:28.999
l mean. popularity is so much better
than being treated like a social leper.

158
00:14:29.610 --> 00:14:33.478
Popularity's a job. Alvin.
Not a privilege.

159
00:14:33.548 --> 00:14:35.448
lt's nothing but work and worries.

160
00:14:35.683 --> 00:14:39.050
Work to get in. work to stay in.

161
00:14:39.420 --> 00:14:41.581
Get a clue.

162
00:14:53.601 --> 00:14:55.592
You're killing them. dog.

163
00:15:00.708 --> 00:15:03.074
Morning. dime pieces.

164
00:15:03.978 --> 00:15:06.412
Your gear is real tight today. boo.

165
00:15:06.614 --> 00:15:11.950
Appreciate it. You know.
Nike. Burberry. Gucci. Scooby-Doo.

166
00:15:12.887 --> 00:15:15.515
You're taking me to Jerry's
Friday night. right?

167
00:15:15.990 --> 00:15:19.619
Sure. l mean...

168
00:15:19.894 --> 00:15:23.762
...how could l say no
to a breezy like you?

169
00:15:23.998 --> 00:15:25.556
For real?

170
00:15:25.733 --> 00:15:29.863
Real is all l am. baby.

171
00:15:31.005 --> 00:15:32.973
l'll holler.

172
00:15:36.677 --> 00:15:40.943
Yvonne. he just broke up with Paris
less than 24 hours ago.

173
00:15:41.983 --> 00:15:43.917
You just mad l beat you to him.

174
00:15:50.124 --> 00:15:54.891
It's Yvonne.
You're all mine tomorrow night.

175
00:15:56.797 --> 00:15:58.025
You know. Yolanda. my big girl.
we're gonna need the whole back seat.

176
00:16:00.501 --> 00:16:04.835
Girls are gonna let us. They're gonna let us.
is what l'm saying. when they see this.

177
00:16:05.039 --> 00:16:08.531
-Amazing.
-Came out all right. no thanks to you.

178
00:16:08.709 --> 00:16:10.677
Feel the seats. Alvin.

179
00:16:14.081 --> 00:16:16.072
All right. Got the Phat Farm hookup...

180
00:16:17.084 --> 00:16:20.986
...shag carpet. laptop. minibar. Wow.

181
00:16:21.689 --> 00:16:25.022
Wait till you see the routine
we got worked out to get in the car.

182
00:16:25.193 --> 00:16:27.684
Here. Stand in the front.
Come on. hurry up.

183
00:16:27.895 --> 00:16:29.726
Look. right there.

184
00:16:55.122 --> 00:16:56.714
Doors.

185
00:17:11.172 --> 00:17:14.664
You know. you guys should really
clean out the carburetor.

186
00:17:15.209 --> 00:17:19.202
Ben's got an old Holley four-barrel
at the shop. l think he'll let me get it.

187
00:17:20.047 --> 00:17:22.914
-Cool.
-We're cruising tonight.

188
00:17:24.185 --> 00:17:27.780
l can get right on it. l'll go down there
right now. have it fixed.

189
00:17:28.656 --> 00:17:32.217
-l really wanna roll out with you guys.
-For real? Right on.

190
00:17:32.693 --> 00:17:33.853
We missed you. man.

191
00:17:34.028 --> 00:17:37.794
We've been checking the GM website.
hoping to see your update.

192
00:17:39.033 --> 00:17:41.126
Hey. there's plenty of time for that.

193
00:17:41.502 --> 00:17:46.064
l'll meet you all at Kenneth's house at 8.
We gonna party. Go put on your good stuff.

194
00:17:47.008 --> 00:17:49.738
-l don't have any good stuff.
-lt's all right.

195
00:17:57.752 --> 00:18:00.812
Hey. yo. man. l'm digging the whip. boy.

196
00:18:03.190 --> 00:18:05.522
l'm feeling it. man.

197
00:18:05.660 --> 00:18:07.252
You got the hooptie.

198
00:18:08.929 --> 00:18:10.920
Look at her.

199
00:18:11.999 --> 00:18:16.595
Yeah. l'm like the Renaissance man
of automobiles. You feel me?

200
00:18:16.804 --> 00:18:22.606
This here is my newest work of art.
l call this the "groupie hooptie."

201
00:18:25.146 --> 00:18:26.670
This is hot.

202
00:18:28.149 --> 00:18:30.947
Put a microwave
in the glove compartment.

203
00:18:34.055 --> 00:18:36.751
Oh. no. Oh. no.

204
00:18:38.559 --> 00:18:42.552
-He's doing it.
-Get some. Quench your thirst on that.

205
00:18:46.901 --> 00:18:49.131
He's 63 and a half minutes late.
lt's not like him.

206
00:19:24.171 --> 00:19:25.798
Where you going in such a hurry?

207
00:19:28.876 --> 00:19:31.868
-No rush.
-l get free long distance on my cell. baby.

208
00:19:32.079 --> 00:19:33.569
l don't need it on a date.

209
00:19:37.952 --> 00:19:40.045
ls your foot on the gas?

210
00:19:43.224 --> 00:19:44.191
Sorry.

211
00:19:44.358 --> 00:19:45.985
Now...

212
00:19:48.362 --> 00:19:49.761
...where were we?

213
00:19:50.965 --> 00:19:52.330
You gotta relax. Al.

214
00:19:52.800 --> 00:19:54.700
lt's all right.

215
00:19:54.902 --> 00:19:58.998
Now. don't you worry. because
Mama's gonna take good care of you.

216
00:20:25.866 --> 00:20:27.891
-l was just e-mailing you.
-Sure you were.

217
00:20:28.102 --> 00:20:32.732
No. seriously. man. l'm telling you. you will
not believe what happened to me tonight.

218
00:20:32.940 --> 00:20:34.635
Give us the keys to our car.

219
00:20:35.910 --> 00:20:39.402
Okay. but l'm telling you.
it's coming out like a Penthouse letter.

220
00:20:43.684 --> 00:20:47.085
Y'all know how it is when you're
butt-naked with a little cutie. right?

221
00:20:48.122 --> 00:20:50.090
Yeah. right--

222
00:20:50.324 --> 00:20:54.055
We were worried. We thought you might
be at Ben's working on our car.

223
00:20:54.228 --> 00:20:58.130
-We went down there. but it was closed.
-Took an hour to get his home number.

224
00:20:58.933 --> 00:21:00.423
-You talked to Ben?
-Yeah.

225
00:21:00.801 --> 00:21:05.135
He says if you don't come in soon.
the camshaft's going back to Germany.

226
00:21:05.372 --> 00:21:09.331
-Oh.
-That's right. "Oh."

227
00:21:11.712 --> 00:21:13.339
Look. Let me explain this--

228
00:21:13.714 --> 00:21:17.309
As of midnight. we're officially
excommunicating Alvin from the clubhouse.

229
00:21:17.718 --> 00:21:20.778
The clubhouse from fourth-freaking-grade?
You can't be serious.

230
00:21:20.955 --> 00:21:23.856
We shall never again speak to.
nor respond to any words...

231
00:21:24.024 --> 00:21:27.460
-...from the aforementioned Alvin Johnson.
-Chuck. man.

232
00:21:27.828 --> 00:21:30.922
Three. two. one.

233
00:21:31.098 --> 00:21:33.362
Walter.

234
00:21:36.737 --> 00:21:37.965
Fine. then.

235
00:21:38.172 --> 00:21:41.005
Dude. l don't need you losers.

236
00:21:42.910 --> 00:21:44.935
Ain't my fault
you guys ain't getting no--

237
00:21:45.145 --> 00:21:47.807
Boobie? All you gave him
was a little boob action?

238
00:21:48.015 --> 00:21:49.141
That was all he wanted.

239
00:21:49.850 --> 00:21:52.478
-Was it good?
-l was good.

240
00:21:53.387 --> 00:21:57.448
Hello. What happened to the pact that we
wouldn't date each other's ex-boyfriends?

241
00:21:57.858 --> 00:22:02.386
